article.headline: IUPUI 86, Urbana 69
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- George Hill scored a career-high 32 points and grabbed 15 rebounds and IUPUI dominated the second half to beat Urbana 86-69 Monday night. Brandon Cole scored 21 points for the Jaguars (5-5). Hill was 10-of-16 from the field and 12-of-13 from the free-throw line. Marques Fobbs led the Blue Knights (5-7) with 20 points. Robert Harris scored 17 and Joe Williams 10 for Urbana. The Blue Knights led 26-25 when Harris fouled IUPUI's David Barlow with 5:22 left in the first half. Barlow sank two free throws to put the Jaguars up by one and ignited a 14-9 run that gave IUPUI a 41-35 halftime lead. The Jaguars never trailed during the second half and Urbana got no closer than seven. IUPUI dominated the Blue Knights inside, outscoring them 38-28 in the paint and outrebounding Urbana 35-25. The Jaguars also scored more points off turnovers (25-10) and scored more second-chance points (19-9).
